Uses of Package
Maze

  • Classes in Maze used by Maze 
    Class and Description
    Cell
    Cell class which describes a cell object that contains a north, east, south, and west wall as well as information that describes whether it is a cell that is visible, visited, or it's type (border, time point, end point, etc...).
    Character
    Character class which contains information on how a character object (player) should behave; handles movement upon input, collisions and redraw functions.
    GamePanel
    JPanel extension which handles the main game loop, updates and drawing to the screen.
    GenMaze
    Recursively generates a maze by "destroying" or hiding walls in each Cell object in a two dimensional array.
    GraphicsMaze
    Generates a graphical representation of the GenMaze object.
    InputHandler
    This class handles the input events, mainly, key press and release events.
    MoveHandler
    MoveHandler specification that all InputHandlers (regardless of input type) must meet in order for the character object to correctly move.
    RectCell
    RectCell represents an object that contains graphical information (Rectangle objects) on a specific cell.
